name: On the way
description:
Mexico City prepares year after year to welcome millions of Guadeloupean pilgrims who arrive from various parts of the country and abroad to celebrate the Virgin of Guadalupe on December 12.

From the eve to the Feast of the Virgin of Guadalupe, millions of pilgrims come to the Basilica, at the foot of Tepeyac, to be able to see and pray before the image, which appeared to Juan Diego.
